          ]
        },
        "text": [
          " اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ أَ لَمْ نَجْعَلِ الْأَرْضَ كِفاتاً أَحْياءً وَ أَمْواتاً قَالَ دَفْنُ الشَّعْرِ وَ الظُّفُرِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ibn Fazzal, from one of his companions, from Abu Kahmas, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding the Words of Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic <span class=\"ibTxt\"><a href=\"/#/books/quran:77#h25\">[77:25]</a> Have We not made the earth as a place <a href=\"/#/books/quran:77#h26\">[77:26]</a> For the living and the dead</span>. He<sup>asws</sup> said: Burying of the hair and the nails’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "1. A number of our people have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from ibn Faddal from certain persons of his people from abu Kahmas who have said the following: “About the meaning of the words of Allah, most Majestic, most Glorious, ’Have We not made the earth a collector (homes) of dead and living/ <a href=\"/#/books/quran:77#h25\">[77:25]</a> abu ’Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ’It is a reference to burying of the hairs and fingernails/” "
          ]
        }
      }
